{"id":735481,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Haakon_Chevalier","text":"=\"preserve\">Haakon Maurice Chevalier (September 10, 1901 \u2013 July 4, 1985) was an American author, translator, and professor of French literature at the University of California, Berkeley best known for his friendship with physicist J. Robert Oppenheimer, whom he met at Berkeley, California in 1937. He translated many works by Salvador Dal\u00ED, Andr\u00E9 Malraux, Vladimir Pozner, Louis Aragon, Frantz Fanon and Victor Vasarely into English.\nChevalier was born on September 10, 1901 in Lakewood Township, New Jersey and died on July 4, 1985 in Paris at the age of 83.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"United_States","surface_form":"American","offset":80},{"uri":"Author","surface_form":"author","offset":89},{"uri":"Translator","surface_form":"translator","offset":97},{"uri":"French_literature","surface_form":"French literature","offset":126},{"uri":"University_of_California%2C_Berkeley","surface_form":"University of California, Berkeley","offset":151},{"uri":"Physicist","surface_form":"physicist","offset":221},{"uri":"J._Robert_Oppenheimer","surface_form":"J. Robert Oppenheimer","offset":231},{"uri":"Berkeley%2C_California","surface_form":"Berkeley, California","offset":269},{"uri":"Salvador_Dal%C3%AD","surface_form":"Salvador Dal\u00ED","offset":327},{"uri":"Andr%C3%A9_Malraux","surface_form":"Andr\u00E9 Malraux","offset":342},{"uri":"Vladimir_Salomonovitch_Pozner","surface_form":"Vladimir Pozner","offset":357},{"uri":"Louis_Aragon","surface_form":"Louis Aragon","offset":374},{"uri":"Frantz_Fanon","surface_form":"Frantz Fanon","offset":388},{"uri":"Victor_Vasarely","surface_form":"Victor Vasarely","offset":405},{"uri":"English_language","surface_form":"English","offset":426},{"uri":"Lakewood_Township%2C_New_Jersey","surface_form":"Lakewood Township","offset":479},{"uri":"New_Jersey","surface_form":"New Jersey","offset":498},{"uri":"Paris","surface_form":"Paris","o